LedToggle library implements a library for led toggling 
It provides an Handle method to be used in the loop or Ticker interrupt service routine
After having created an istance of the class, the settings must be given in the setup by means Set method.
It take several parameters: void Set(int pin, LedType ledAct, uint32_t Ton_ms, uint32_t Toff_ms)
Led Type is a type to specify the led active state (high or low).
After the settings the Start method activate the led control.
You can stop the control and also read the led status
The example uses a state machine to change the toggling periods in order to have a kind of blinking code scheme (example to indicate the states of WiFi link)
